This directory contains helpful setup scripts for running the Usint Flask Application on local host for testing changes.


localhost --- tcsh script which will set environment variables necessary for logging in,
	      operating on the test Ocat revision database, and for sending python error messages
	      directly to the web browser.

localhostMAIL --- tcsh script same as localhost, however it will configured the app to send
		  error messages via email from the UsintErrorHandler directly to the configured admin email


Note that this script is included for convenience, but this directory does not natively contain the setup 
necessary for a developer to test this application on their own git branch. To setup that ability,
copy this directory to some other testing directory available to the developer, then symlink the necessary files
into the testCUSFlask directory so that localhost/localhostMAIL will operate on the correct git branch. For example...

[waaron@scrapper-11:55:testCUSFlask]$ pwd
/data/mta4/waaron/testCUSFlask
[waaron@scrapper-11:55:testCUSFlask]$ ls -lha
